Qatar Fertilizer to Shut Ammonia Plant for 3 Weeks, ICIS Says

-- B y   R o b e r t   T u t t l e
-- 
2011-03-02T12:58:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/qatar-fertilizer-to-shut-ammonia-plant-for-3-weeks-icis-says.html
Qatar Fertilizer Co., a unit of
Industries Qatar, plans to shut its No. 2 ammonia and urea plant
on March 5 for three weeks, Chemical Industry News &
Intelligence said, citing an unidentified company official.  The company had previously said about 500 tonnes a day of
ammonia exports would be lost during the shutdown, ICIS said.
The plant can produce 900 tonnes a day of ammonia and 1,000
tonnes a day of urea, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Tuttle in Doha at 
 rtuttle@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss on   sev@bloomberg.net  